,Recommended,282050,28215313,"Posted: 5 December, 2016",all,Mugman,"It's eh. I would recommend it if you can get it with all the DLC for less than $20. Otherwise Reflex is pretty fun too and has more to do (offroad races, Freeride challenges, etc)Graphics are nice, the tracks are really well built, the game runs amazing (on both my computer with a GTX 1080, and my friend's computer with a 1050), the multiplayer is pretty good when there are people playing, the connection is pretty solid, AND YOU CAN PLAY WITH A MANUAL TRANSMISSION! Granted you don't use the clutch to shift but I think you can if you wanna be that realistic.A few issues: The physics are wonky at times, the known ""whip glitch"" that as far as I know Rainbow is working on fixing (at least it seems that way from the bug report thread) and scrubs are really hard (but maybe I just suck). Also the first person camera is pretty♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ it's more realistic than Reflex but sometimes you can see through your arms. Although maybe it's just the FOV/resolution I play at.Coming from an actual rider I would give this game a 7/10. Maybe some would have a hard time with this game, but it's pretty enjoyable, although a little hard to recommend for $30 without any DLC. Steam Summer Sale is coming up soon though! Hope the 2017 SX pack goes on sale."
